description:
&lt;p&gt;This is an exciting opportunity to work as part of our integrated therapy team on the Acute Stroke Unit (Ward 6B) at the John Radcliffe Hospital. The unit specialises in the acute rehabilitation, patient’s ongoing rehabilitation is delivered in a different location. Our average length of stay is 5 days.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will be required to work alongside Occupational Therapists, Physiotherapists and Speech and Language Therapists, to carry out prescribed treatments with patients to facilitate their intensive rehabilitation and discharge from hospital (60% of the time).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Alongside the clinical work the post holder will carry out essential administrative duties that will include uploading accurate stroke data to Stroke Sentinel National Audit Programme (SSNAP) to ensure robust statistical information is produced weekly, monthly, and in line with Department of Health guidelines, supporting Stroke Therapists and Stroke Nurse Specialists (40%).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applicants need to have well developed interpersonal and organizational skills. A more than basic computer skills with experience of excel is advantageous.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Closing date 11th November 2020&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
